	<h3>Related Documents</h3>      
	<ul>
	
	<li><a href="/en/consumer_affairs/consumer_protection/consumer_rights/consumers_and_the_law_in_ireland.html">Your rights as a consumer in Ireland</a><br>In Ireland, the rights of consumers are protected by Irish and EU laws.  Consumer legislation is described here along with information about deposits and redress mechanisms.</li>
	
	<li><a href="/en/consumer_affairs/consumer_protection/consumer_complaints/replacements_refunds_and_credit_notes.html">Replacements, refunds and credit notes</a><br>If you buy unfit or faulty goods and you complain successfully to the retailer you are entitled to a replacement, a repair or a refund.  This document explains what your rights are with regard to refunds.</li>
	
	<li><a href="/en/consumer_affairs/consumer_protection/consumer_rights/distance_selling.html">Shopping from home</a><br>This document discusses the rules governing distance selling, whether it involves selling via the Internet, e-mail, fax, telephone, mail order.  It tells you what your rights are when you shop online.</li>
	
	</ul>	
